library(dplyr) library(readr) library(quantmod) company<-"SHIB-USD" mktcap<-getQuote(company, what = yahooQF(c("Market Capitalization")))[,2] mktcap<-mktcap * 10^-9 stDt <- as.Date(Sys.time()) endDt <- as.Date("2022-08-31") remainingCloses<-sum(!weekdays(seq(stDt, endDt, "days")) %in% c("Saturday", "Sunday")) forecastBands <- c(-Inf,15,25,35,45,55,Inf) histData<-read_csv( paste0( "https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v7/finance/download/" , company , "?period1=1633392000&period2=" #start from 5/10/2021 when spot went permanently above 0.000010 , floor(as.numeric(as.POSIXct(Sys.time()))) , "&interval=1d&events=history&includeAdjustedClose=true" ) ) pricehistory<-as.numeric(histData$`Adj Close`) pricehistory<-pricehistory[!is.na(pricehistory)] sdMovementRatio <- sd(log(pricehistory[1:length(pricehistory)-1]/pricehistory[2:(length(pricehistory))])) simulation<-mktcap*replicate(10000, cumprod(exp(rnorm( remainingCloses,mean = 0, sd = sdMovementRatio/2 )))[remainingCloses]) cutSimulation<-as_tibble(cut(simulation,forecastBands)) mutate(count(cutSimulation,value),n/sum(n))

I'm very skeptical of Shiba Inu's future. It's a meme of a meme, which gave it some initial momentum (as well at astronomical returns this past year!), but the technology behind this particular cryptocurrency is not strong when compared to coins like Solana, so I suspect Shiba Inu will lose favor with investors within the next few months as the initial buzz of excitement wears off, and I don't think it will have much use besides as a speculative asset. Furthermore, I'm quite bearish of the crypto market in general right now, so I see the crypto market overall taking a hit over the next several months.

Why Shiba Inu is making noise? 1) SHIB soared more than tenfold in October 2021, placing it in the top 10 of all cryptocurrencies 2) Elon Musk tweeted a picture of his new Shiba Inu puppy Floki in the first week of October 3) Crypto investors were enthused by the launch of Shiba Inu NFTs, as well as unconfirmed rumors that SHIB would be listed on popular stock and crypto trading app Robinhood.
It's a meme coin. The fad will fade.
